

                                      ; Tic Tac toe
                                      ; Guy Fedorkow
                                      ; Sep 26, 2024


                                      ; Simple game of tic-tac-toe written in Whirlwind assembly code.
                                      ; The game displays on the WW CRT, and can be played with the light gun
                                      ; As of Sep 26, it was a two-person game, i.e., i alternates X and O plays
                                      ; I then changed it to a person-against-computer with a complex recursive algorithm
                                      ; Mar 2026 - I then rewrote the game algorithm with help from Claude.ai
                                      ;     - it's *much* faster, with no look-ahead
                                      ;     - but there's at least one way to beat the machine (as implied in DCL-105 as well)
                                      ; Jul 3, 2026 - not a rewrite, but an overhaul:
                                      ;     - added MIR switch input method (as in DCL-105) in parallel with the light gun input.  Watch
                                      ;         for off-by-one confusion; the game algorithm numbers cells 0-8, DCL-105 uses switches 1-9.
                                      ;     - caused the game status line to flash once showing the computer's turn; i.e., the computer-move
                                      ;         finishes in one refresh cycle
                                      ;     - added "autoclick", a compile-time mode to make the game play against a pre-set table of moves,
                                      ;         to be used in "attract" mode at HNF.  Uncomment the TS at turn-on-autoclick to make this take effect
                                      ;     - changed so that the User's move shows as X and the computer's as O


                                      ; Geometry
                                      ; the basic game board is laid out on a 16x16 grid as follows:

                                      ;  cell 0   | cell 1   |  cell 2
                                      ;  @(4,12)  | @(8,12)  |  @(12,12)
                                      ; --------------------------------
                                      ;  cell 3   | cell 4   |  cell 5
                                      ;  @(4,8)   | @(8,8)   |  @(12,8)
                                      ; --------------------------------
                                      ;  cell 6   | cell 7   |  cell 8
                                      ;  @(4,4)   | @(8,4)   |  @(12,4)

                                      ;----------- old layout ----------
                                      ;  cell 6   | cell 7   |  cell 8
                                      ;  @(4,12)  | @(8,12)  |  @(12,12)
                                      ; --------------------------------
                                      ;  cell 3   | cell 4   |  cell 5
                                      ;  @(4,8)   | @(8,8)   |  @(12,8)
                                      ; --------------------------------
                                      ;  cell 0   | cell 1   |  cell 2
                                      ;  @(4,4)   | @(8,4)   |  @(12,4)
                                      ;-------------------------------

